cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.PL 

This paper involves the use of agent modelling and game-playing strategies, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), game theory (cs.GT), and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS) and Information Set MCTS (IS-MCTS) also suggests a potential fit for the sub-category of stochastic optimization and learning (cs.SI). Finally, the creation of rule-based agents falls under the sub-category of programming languages (cs.PL).
